{
  "texts": [
    "For each conformal structure c on B 2, there is a homeomorphismM(Σ, G) ≃ Hom red (π 1 (B), G)/G,where M(Σ, G) is the space of K C -gauge equivalence classes of polystable G-Higgs bundles, Σ = (B, c).We note that this correspondence is Aut(Σ)-equivariant.",
    "Here, Aut(Σ) acts on M(Σ, G) by pull-back, and on Hom red (π 1 (B), G)/G by pre-composition with the induced action on the fundamental group.In order to explain the gauge-invariant condition on Higgs bundles that detects conformality of ρequivariant harmonic maps, we describe briefly how a reductive representation ρ ∈ Hom red (π 1 (B), G) gives rise to a Higgs bundle.Given ρ ∈ Hom red (π 1 (B), G), let h: Σ → (G/K, g sym) be a ρ-equivariant harmonic map (which exists by Theorem 4.2).",
    "Let E R = Σ × ρ R n be the flat vector bundle associated to ρ (recall that ρ(π 1 (B)) ≤ G ≤ SL n (R)), and E = E R ⊗ C its complexification.",
    "Then h: Σ → G/K ⊂ SL n (R)/ SO(n) defines a bundle metric on E R, and its differential dh defines a section h -1 dh ∈ Ω 1 (Σ, End 0 (E R)).",
    "The Higgs field Φ is the (1, 0)-part of the complex-linear extension h -1 dh C ∈ Ω 1 C (Σ, End 0 (E))."
  ]
}